parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive rust and corrosion on the frame can lead to structural failure, compromising the vehicle's safety and integrity, potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Rust and corrosion on the frame
subframe
and suspension components
including control arms and support brackets
causing structural weakness and potentially leading to loss of control or failure of critical components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tailgate latch can cause the door to open unexpectedly, potentially leading to accidents or injuries, and can also cause difficulties in opening or closing the door.
symptoms: Melted or eroded rubber components
sticky or tar-like substance on the handle
difficulty opening or closing the tailgate
and unexpected door opening.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure due to Master Cylinder/ABS Module Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder or ABS module can cause the brake pedal to travel to the floor, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal travels to the floor
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
ABS system warning light illuminates
vehicle pulls to one side while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially when the vehicle is unable to be stopped or controlled.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
often when the brake pedal is pressed
and may continue to accelerate even when the accelerator pedal is not depressed. The engine RPM may increase rapidly
and the vehicle may lurch forward or surge ahead.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Floor mat interference can cause unintended acceleration, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The floor mat may interfere with the accelerator pedal
causing it to stick or become stuck
leading to unintended acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A sticking accelerator pedal can cause unintended acceleration, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal may stick or become stuck
causing the vehicle to accelerate suddenly and uncontrollably.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration caused by the air conditioner can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially when the vehicle is unable to be stopped or controlled.
symptoms: The vehicle may surge forward or accelerate suddenly when the air conditioner is turned on
especially when the fan speed is high.
